The paper presents a new approach for solving a nurse scheduling problem using evolutionary algorithms and heuristics. This problem falls under the category of optimization and scheduling, which is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The use of evolutionary algorithms also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of constructive heuristics and local optimality criteria, which are common techniques in data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
